Brief question about a name...
by TokonatsuHana » Sun 07.03.2011 3:22 am Hello! So I've had the screen name "Tokonatsu" for years, and recently I just changed it to TokonatsuHana... The problem is that I originally made it with no real knowledge of Japanese, and now I'm wondering just how random it sounds to someone who actually knows the language. As far as I've learned, the kanji for it is 常夏花　or more like 常夏の花 which to me looks like it would mean "flower of everlasting summer" or "tropical flower." But when I was talking to some American Japanese students they said it looks like "tonkatsu" which is a kind of sliced pork >.< I guess what I'm trying to ask is, does my screen name actually live up to the meaning I originally hoped it had, or is it just a senseless mash of kanji? I'd appreciate any opinions or help! Thank you very much for reading this, and have a great night!
TokonatsuHana
