Re: Brief question about a name...
by Hyperworm » Sun 07.03.2011 1:00 pm I think that 常夏の花 sounds better than without the の (concatenated, I start wondering about rendaku and other stuff).But if the question is "Does 'tokonatsu' sound right at all?", I don't see any problem with it. It's a valid word, with more than just a passing mention in the dictionary, and sounds poetic. Even if you don't know 常(とこ), 夏(なつ) jumps out at you from the romaji, and 花 makes that connection even more obvious.'Tonkatsu' is obviously a much more common word, and there might be a little similarity there, but I think ribbing the name for it is just being silly. ._.
