Re: Brief question about a name...
by Ongakuka » Tue 07.05.2011 3:05 pm If it's a name, I don't see any necessity for having a の. In old Japanese, names which included the particle の could be written without it, right? It probably feels more 'poetic' and like correct Japanese if it is there, I suppose.
なぜなら、おまえは・・・・・・人形だ
